# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code when working with Salesforce DX projects using the sfdx-iq plugin.

## Architecture (v2.0.2)

Commands are **self-contained** — each command includes its domain standards inline. No context loading step required. Invoke commands directly; agents are delegated to for domain-specific review.

- **Installed profile**: {{ACTIVE_PROFILE_NAME}}

## Core Principles

1. **Governor-Limits-First** — Every code change is evaluated against Salesforce governor limits
2. **Security-First** — CRUD/FLS enforcement, `with sharing` by default, no SOQL injection
3. **Test-Driven** — 75% minimum coverage (90%+ target), test-first development
4. **Bulkification Always** — All code must handle 200+ records in trigger context
5. **Agent-First** — Delegate to specialized agents for domain tasks
6. **Plan Before Execute** — Plan complex features before writing code

## Available Commands

**Domain Commands** (flag-driven lifecycle):

| Command | Flags | Purpose |
|---------|-------|---------|
| `/apex-class` | `--new`, `--review`, `--refine`, `--bug-fix` | Service, Selector, Controller, Domain, Utility classes |
| `/trigger` | `--new`, `--review`, `--refine`, `--bug-fix` | Triggers + handler classes |
| `/async-apex` | `--new`, `--refine`, `--bug-fix` | Batch, Queueable, Schedulable, @future, Platform Events |
| `/integration-apex` | `--new`, `--refine`, `--bug-fix` | REST/SOAP callouts, inbound services |
| `/lwc` | `--new`, `--explain`, `--refine`, `--bug-fix` | Lightning Web Components |
| `/flow` | `--new`, `--review`, `--refine`, `--explain` | Salesforce Flows |
| `/code-review` | `--apex`, `--lwc`, `--flow`, `--*-all` | Full code review via specialized agents |
| `/explain` | `--apex`, `--lwc`, `--flow`, `--deep` | Explain artifacts |
| `/security-scan` | — | CRUD/FLS, sharing, injection, XSS |
| `/data-model` | — | ER design, object relationships |

**Utility Commands:**

- `/apex-test` — Create or improve Apex test classes with coverage targeting
- `/debug-log` — Retrieve and analyze Salesforce debug logs
- `/org-health` — Org health: security score, metadata debt
- `/plan` — Implementation planning
- `/package` — 2GP package management
- `/handoff` — Generate session summary for context handoff
- `/setup-project` — Initialize plugin config for this project
- `/status` / `/doctor` / `/repair` / `/csiq-help` — CLI utilities

## CLI Tools

- `npx sfdx-iq help` — Show available CLI commands
- `npx sfdx-iq setup-project` — Copy config to an SFDX project
- `npx sfdx-iq status` — Check plugin and org status
- `npx sfdx-iq doctor` — Diagnose configuration issues
- `npx sfdx-iq repair` — Auto-fix common configuration problems

## Development Notes

- All Apex must use `with sharing` unless explicitly justified
- All SOQL must use bind variables or `WITH USER_MODE` / `WITH SECURITY_ENFORCED`
- No SOQL or DML in loops — ever
- One trigger per object with handler delegation
- Permission sets over profiles

## Hook Configuration

Quality-gate hooks run on file save for `.cls`, `.trigger`, `lwc/**`, and `*.flow-meta.xml`.

- `CSIQ_HOOK_PROFILE=minimal|standard|strict` — scope of checks (default: `standard`)
- `CSIQ_DISABLED_HOOKS="rule1,rule2"` — disable individual rules

## Salesforce Governor Limits Reference

| Limit | Synchronous | Asynchronous |
|-------|-------------|--------------|
| SOQL Queries | 100 | 200 |
| DML Statements | 150 | 150 |
| CPU Time | 10,000 ms | 60,000 ms |
| Heap Size | 6 MB | 12 MB |
| Callouts | 100 | 100 |
| Future Calls | 50 | 0 (in future) |
| SOQL Rows | 50,000 | 50,000 |
| DML Rows | 10,000 | 10,000 |
